></tr><tr><td><span>D</span></td><td><span>63.5</span></td></tr><tr><td><sp=
an>D-</span></td><td><span>60</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>F</span></td><t=
d><span>=E2=80=94</span></td></tr></tbody></table><p>So those are the minim=
um percentages I use. In most courses, I grade individual assignments on a =
scale of 0 to 100, and then at the end of the semester I use Blackboard or =
Excel to compute each student=E2=80=99s final average to the nearest hundre=
dth of a percentage point. So, in practice, my grading scale is as follows:=
</p><table class=3D"table"><tbody><tr><th colspan=3D"2"><span>Table 10:</sp=
an></th></tr><tr><td><span>letter grade</span></td><td><span>percentage ran=
ge</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>A</span></td><td><span>93.50 and above</sp=
